Over the course of the entire game, Ohtani created a total of 0.2354888 in run value. The negative run value created in his first, third, and fourth at-bats (i.e., when he got out) is offset by the positive run value he created by singling in the top of the 3rd inning and driving in a run in the top of the 8th inning. Note the run value of his last at-at is exactly 1 because a single run scored but the base-runner configuration did not change as a result of the at-bat.
